nts1.d: Awe is something you feel when confronted with forces beyond your control: nature, the cosmos, chaos, human error, hallucinations.

12th Isle co-founder Fergus Clark runs a monthly session through chaotic record shelves, tascam nightmares, label related tracks and unreleased music from the global sphere.
From the host: "One hour of roots, dub and love songs "

nts1.n: CHANNELING W/ IVAN SMAGGHE & NATHAN GREGORY WILKINS
nts1.d: Old friends and hapless mavericks Ivan Smagghe and Nathan Gregory Wilkins present a fortnightly window into their ramshackle musical world. A show with absolutely no rules (as they'd only break them). We love the unmixable, old & new. We are oddballs and we love you.

Audio-visual adventurer Trevor Jackson presents a broad spectrum of brand new experimental music, along with ancient oddities of every perceivable genre. A fortnightly uncompromising journey into the unexpected.
Music for sick minds and warm hearts
The French producer, DJ & Work In Progress 2019 alumna Crystallmess is Unleashed - bleeding edge club sounds & emotional content every month.

nts1.n: OPEN HAND REAL FLAMES - new music for gamelan

OPEN HAND REAL FLAMES is a monthly show presented by Bass Clef. Each episode has a theme - usually a specific musical instrument or process, perhaps an artist or composer, sometimes a record label. Ranging wide over centuries and genres, looking for connections and joy. Always welcomes contributions, music, suggestions.

The Utrecht native from the Netherlands Carista, joins us to share music of all kinds going from Soul, Jazz, House and everything in between.

Mr. Big Happy is a graphic designer, artist, DJ, and music archivist from San Francisco, California. While he is an accomplished designer and artist, over the years he has always had a love for music and spends time searching for rare and obscure vinyl. Big Happy’s focus is the late 70s into the late 80s - modern soul, funk, boogie and disco.

nts2.n: Sounds of Barranquilla Carnival w/ Calamidades Lola
nts2.d: Barranquilla native Calamidades Lola selects one hour of sounds from Colombian Carnival, featuring cumbia, guaracha and folk records.

nts2.n: MUSIC FOR A HEALING EARTH W/ THE COSMIC TONES RESEARCH TRIO
nts2.d:
Healing and restorative sonic transmissions for all beings.
From the host: "Black History Month edition"

Cultural virtuoso and creative luminary SHABAZZ, aka DJ Auntie Spice, illuminates obscure nostalgic treasures, crafting a rich, diverse auditory experience of soul, funk, jazz and beyond with her sound art initiative, Auntie·ism.
From the host: "This mix centers Black soul as a living, moving practice in honor of Black History Month. Shaped by funk, house, garage, and early electronic traditions, it carries joy, affirmation, and intimacy—reassurance music, church and discothèque in one breath."

Phil Cho & Russell Alexander share monthly recordings from their hilltop soundsystem in Echo Park, California. 
From the host: "First hour featuring Zillas on Acid!"

The eclectic and diverse frequencies from a true East Bay Area native, Abby Imperial is ready to bring the soulful sounds of Rnb, g-funk, deep house, jungle & more..
From the host: "All Glory be to God!!!!"

btwn Earth+Sky is Lara Sarkissian's conceptual platform in which sound and music are prioritized across visual art realms and immersive experiences. Sonically, the label encourages collaboration between electronic music producers and musicians, to create ephemeral, once in a lifetime recordings and live performance. Lara Sarkissian is a sound artist, electronic composer, filmmaker and former cofounder of label CLUB CHAI. Emerging from multidisciplinary practices, she invites you into her world of music spanning across genres and regions which inspire her production; sounds encountered from film, archives, the dance/electronic underground and Armenian, SWANA performance communities.
From the host: "Slowed + reverbed, cloud rap, euphoric trance r&b edits"

nts2.n: Night Shift w/ Diamondstein & Isamaya Ffrench
nts2.d:
Cold winds, empty street. Diamondstein, member of the band Melted Bodies, presents Night Shift - ambient techno, sinister industrial sounds, and moody experimental music for night time noir moments.
From the host: "Isamaya Ffrench is a make-up artist largely known for uniquely beautiful and grotesque ideas largely inspired by gore, horror, and the macabre. However, I was introduced to her amazing work in the band Alto Arc. She has a unique mind for how sound and visual ideas collide, and this show reflects it."

subtle.d: Tripta is a Toronto based producer/DJ focusing on the darker sounds of Grime. Also blending elements of Drill, Dubstep and even Jungle all together for a unique sound you won't hear anywhere else. Signed to Slimzee's 'Slimzo's Recordings' and ‘Rotpot Records’.

Sound Arkitek is a Chicago hip-hop DJ with a love for all things drum & bass. 

With over 20 years experience playing house parties, raves, clubs and bars he has an encyclopedic knowledge of music but has always been a participant in jungle culture. In the early 2000s he was exposed to the genre primarily through Dieselboy and Danny The Wildchild mixes as well as the “Jungle Book” series of mixtapes. He became obsessed after hearing Bad Company’s “The Nine” and “Four Days,” as well as Pendulum’s “Vault.” 

As time went on, he got deeper into the scene, going to raves while buying records and posting on Drum & Bass Arena and DNBForum before turning 21 at which point he began going to Lava Lounge for Bass By The Pound’s “Seminar” series. The first legal drum & bass party he attended was Chase & Status at the aforementioned Lava Lounge, and he will never forget the energy when the duo played DJ Hazard’s “Killers Don’t Die” and it got a rewind. His love for the scene led to him playing drum & bass parties, opening for artists like Original Sin, Gridlok, and LTJ Bukem among others. 

His Subtle Radio show is an hour of the finest tunes in the scene at the moment. 

To keep up, follow @djsoundarkitek on Instagram!

Dubversified showcases Canadian West Coast DJ talent specializing in Bass Music. Hosted by Mirage, founder of Dubversified Culture, a community-led organization focusing on music, art, and events. Mirage, originally from Québec, blends house and hip-hop since 2010, now exploring 140bpm and Deep D&B.

subtle.d: Potent Funk records’ Matt Frost - Well known for his technical abilities and Sleazy bass music style, Frost covers all angles from UK alt Rap to the LA beat scene.

Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
BirdE brings an hour of the freshest Drum and Bass covering everything from liquid to techy steppers - the deeper the better.

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.
